<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:03PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Anson,
southwestern Montgomery, northwestern Richmond and southern Stanly
Counties through 500 PM EDT...
At 402 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Midland, or 15 miles north of Monroe, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ansonville, Locust, Norwood, Oakboro, Stanfield, Mount Gilead,
Uwharrie Haven, Blewett Falls Lake, Covington and Pekin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
